				<name type="primary" sortindex="1" value="Alchemy Struggle (アルケミストラグル)" />
			
						                           
						               													<description>&amp;#227;&amp;#130;&amp;#162;&amp;#227;&amp;#131;&amp;#171;&amp;#227;&amp;#130;&amp;#177;&amp;#227;&amp;#131;&amp;#159;&amp;#227;&amp;#130;&amp;#185;&amp;#227;&amp;#131;&amp;#136;&amp;#227;&amp;#131;&amp;#169;&amp;#227;&amp;#130;&amp;#176;&amp;#227;&amp;#131;&amp;#171; (Alchemy Struggle) is a Japanese card game, similar to Goita. It can be played as a 2 or 3 player game, as a 4 player game in partnership.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Players try to develop their potions as alchemists, and the first player who clears out their hand will win.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;To win the game, it is important to determine which color of potion is rare. Because each time you create a potion unique in the world, you can take your turn again. So the players will aim to make potions which require more complex composition.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Further more you should keep in mind that you have a fellow player. By playing cards from your hand onto your partners potions, you will get closer to winning.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;However, be careful, your fellow may secretly keep 'philosopher&amp;rsquo;s stone' card, a wild card in their hand. The philosopher's stone acts like a joker and can complete any potion. Knowing this is in play adds a thrill to the game.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The game was originally published in 2013 by Chicken Dice Games (&amp;#227;&amp;#131;&amp;#129;&amp;#227;&amp;#130;&amp;#173;&amp;#227;&amp;#131;&amp;#179;&amp;#227;&amp;#131;&amp;#128;&amp;#227;&amp;#130;&amp;#164;&amp;#227;&amp;#130;&amp;#185;&amp;#227;&amp;#130;&amp;#178;&amp;#227;&amp;#131;&amp;#188;&amp;#227;&amp;#131;&amp;#160;&amp;#227;&amp;#130;&amp;#186;) and revised and re-issued by Southern Cross Games (&amp;#227;&amp;#130;&amp;#181;&amp;#227;&amp;#130;&amp;#182;&amp;#227;&amp;#131;&amp;#179;&amp;#227;&amp;#130;&amp;#175;&amp;#227;&amp;#131;&amp;#173;&amp;#227;&amp;#130;&amp;#185;&amp;#227;&amp;#130;&amp;#178;&amp;#227;&amp;#131;&amp;#188;&amp;#227;&amp;#131;&amp;#160;&amp;#227;&amp;#130;&amp;#186;) in 2016.&amp;#10;'user summary&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
